  "prompt": "Can pigs show affection?",
  "response": "Yes, pigs can show affection. They are highly intelligent and social animals, and they can form strong bonds with humans and other animals. Pigs may express affection through various behaviors, such as nuzzling, licking, or following their caregivers around. They also communicate through vocalizations and body language, which can indicate their comfort and attachment. Pigs enjoy social interactions and can exhibit playful behavior, further demonstrating their capacity for affection. Overall, they are capable of forming meaningful relationships with those who care for them.",
